        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Make and blind bake the shell",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Make a shortcrust pastry from 200 g {{plain-flour}}, 100 g cold {{unsalted-butter}}, {{fine-salt}}, and 2-3 tbsp cold water. Chill for 30 minutes, then roll out and line a 23 cm pie dish. Trim and chill for 20 minutes. Heat the oven to 200°C (180°C fan). Line the pastry with baking paper and baking beans and blind bake for 15 minutes. Remove the beans and paper and bake for 5 more minutes. Reduce the oven to 180°C (160°C fan).",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Make and bake the filling",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Whisk together the {{whole-eggs}}, {{caster-sugar}}, melted {{unsalted-butter}}, {{buttermilk}}, {{plain-flour}}, {{vanilla-extract}}, and {{lemon-juice}} until smooth and well combined. Pour into the warm blind-baked shell. Bake for 35-40 minutes until the edges are set and the centre has just a slight wobble. The filling will set completely as it cools. Cool in the dish for at least 1 hour before slicing.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
